 sans-serif">filter by difficulty minimum/maximum</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">filter by terrain minimum/maximum</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">keyword search (not just           the title!)</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">filter out caches that have           been completed by certain people (usually yourself)</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">filter by whether or not           a cache has ever been found</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">filter by travelbug</font></li>      </ul>      <p><font color="#3C471E" size="3"><strong>Devices</strong></font></p>      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Through our various file format         support, we allow you to upload your query output to a wide array of devices:</font></p>      <ul>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Palm</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">PocketPC</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Apple iPod</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Cellphone's</font></li>      </ul>      <p><font color="#3C471E" size="3"><strong>Output Formats (Native):</strong></font></p>      <ul>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">html </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">plain text</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">csv - for spreadsheet imports</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">gpspoint - gpspoint datafile</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">vcf - contact format, for           use with iPod's or cellphones</font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">easygps - for GPS units           via <a href="http://www.easygps.com/">EasyGPS</a> or <a href="http://gpsbabel.sourceforge.net/">gpsbabel</a></font></li>      </ul>      <p><font color="#3C471E" size="3"><strong>Output Formats :</strong></font></p>      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">If you have <a href="http://gpsbabel.sourceforge.net/">gpsbabel</a>         installed on your machine, and in the local path, we can make use of many         more formats: </font></p>      <ul>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Cetus for PalmOS </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Navitrak DNA marker </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">GpsDrive </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">GPSman datafile </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">GPSPilot for PalmOS </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">gpsutil </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">GPX XML format </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Holux gm-100 </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> Magellan NAV Companion           for PalmOS </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Magellan MapSend software           </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">MapTech Exchange </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">OziExplorer </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Garmin PCX5 </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Microsoft PocketStreets           2002 Pushpin </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> U.S. Census Bureau Tiger           Mapping Service Data </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> TopoMapPro Places </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">National Geographic Topo           </font></li>        <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Delorme Topo USA4/XMap Conduit